Program: Discovery
Title: The animals of Belize
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p03jrxhk
Last Broadcast Date: 17 September 1999
A report on how scientists are monitoring animals in Belize. A project to protect rare mammals in 40,000 hectares of rainforest in Belize was launched 15 years ago. A reporter goes back to see how the survey has gone. Producer Andrew Luck-Baker.